## What was built

A complete, security-hardened Flask wiki:

```
app.py          Application factory, routes, security headers, error handlers
config.py       Environment-driven config (cookies, secret key, limits)
db.py           SQLite connection + auto schema init (parameterised queries)
forms.py        WTForms (validation + CSRF tokens)
rendering.py    Markdown → bleach-sanitised HTML
schema.sql      users + pages tables
templates/      Auto-escaped Jinja2 views
static/style.css
requirements.txt · README.md · .env.example · .gitignore
```

**Features:** registration/login, create & edit Markdown pages, public read access, a newest-first page index, and title search.

## How the mandatory security requirements are met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | Every query uses `?` placeholders (`db.py`, all routes); `LIKE` search escapes `% _ \` wildcards |
| **Password hashing** | **Argon2id** via `argon2-cffi`, per-user salt, transparent rehash-on-upgrade |
| **XSS** | Jinja2 auto-escaping + Markdown sanitised through a `bleach` allow-list (strips `<script>`, event handlers, `javascript:`/`data:` URLs) + strict CSP |
| **CSRF** | Flask-WTF `CSRFProtect` on every POST (create/edit/login/register/logout); tokens in all forms |
| **Access control / IDOR** | `author_id` checked server-side on edit → 403; `@login_required` on mutations; post-login `next` restricted to local paths |
| **Secure cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (toggleable for local HTTP) |
| **Security headers** | CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, HSTS |
| **No leaked errors** | Custom 400/403/404/500 pages; debug off by default; real exception logged server-side only |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | `SECRET_KEY` read from env, required when `FLASK_ENV=production` |
| **Input validation** | WTForms length/charset validators; 1 MB request cap |

## Run it (port 5036)

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
copy .env.example .env      # keeps SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=0 for local HTTP
python app.py
```

Then open <http://127.0.0.1:5036>. The SQLite DB and tables are created automatically on first run. Register → log in → **New page**.

